    narr:narration """This hub gathers strategic-alignment rubric assessments across the corpus, and the dominant reading is striking uniformity of praise: documents repeatedly score as [exemplary strategic coherence](narr:RubricAssess_StrategicAlignment), with several judged to *be* the strategy rather than merely align to it — [the document IS the strategy](narr:RubricAssess_StrategicAlignment), [worldview as product](narr:Assessment_StrategicAlignment_IPCrisis), and a [positioning thesis tied to every section](narr:RubricAssess_StrategicAlignment_GTM). Recurring anchors are the [Git-native AI memory narrative](narr:RubricAssess_StrategicAlignment_1), mission/vision/positioning/moat, and explicit ties to ADRs ([ADR-001](narr:RubricAssess_Strategy_ADR001), [ADR-002](narr:Assessment_StrategicAlignment_IPCrisis), [ADR-003/005](narr:RubricAssess_StrategicAlignment_ADR002)). The frame shifts from ['tool' to 'infrastructure'](narr:Assessment_Strategy_1), with [network effects as moat](narr:RubricAssess_Strategy_20260107) and [advisor-led GTM](narr:RubricAssess_StrategicAlignment_GTM). Distinct threads sit beneath the consensus: an explicit [rebrand/positioning shift](narr:Assess_Strategy_rebrand), [architecture-domain alignment](narr:Assess_Strategy_cm), and [narrative-architecture principles](narr:Assess_Strategy_collective_memory).""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Assess_Strategy_cm> ;
